<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="U" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Uncertain" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Uncertain</orth> (cf. <emph>Incertain</emph>) 1) doubtful, not to be relied on: <cit><quote>the u. glory of an April day,</quote> <bibl n="shak. tgv 1.3.85" default="NO" valid="yes">Gent. I, 3, 85</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>u. life and sure death,</quote> <bibl n="shak. aww 2.3.20" default="NO" valid="yes">All's II, 3, 20</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>the friends . . . u.</quote> <bibl n="shak. 1h4 2.3.12" default="NO" valid="yes">H4A II, 3, 12</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>u. way of gain,</quote> <bibl n="shak. r3 4.2.64" default="NO" valid="yes">R3 IV, 2, 64</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>the end of war's u.</quote> <bibl n="shak. cor 5.3.141" default="NO" valid="yes">Cor. V, 3, 141</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>in life's u. voyage,</quote> <bibl n="shak. tim 5.1.205" default="NO" valid="yes">Tim. V, 1, 205</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>u. favour,</quote> <bibl n="shak. cym 3.3.64" default="NO" valid="yes">Cymb. III, 3, 64</bibl></cit>.<lb />2) not knowing what to think or do: <cit><quote>the u. sickly appetite,</quote> <bibl n="shak. son 147.4" default="NO" valid="yes">Sonn. 147, 4</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>be not u.</quote> <bibl n="shak. wt 1.2.441" default="NO" valid="yes">Wint. I, 2, 441</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>the people will remain u.</quote> <bibl n="shak. cor 5.6.17" default="NO" valid="yes">Cor. V, 6, 17</bibl></cit>. With <emph>of</emph>: <cit><quote>u. of the issue,</quote> <bibl n="shak. 1h4 1.1.61" default="NO" valid="yes">H4A I, 1, 61</bibl></cit>.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>